Master Answer: HPV vaccine is provided free to males 9 to 26 years of age who have sex with men, including those who may not yet be sexually active and are questioning their sexual orientation. HPV vaccine is available at pharmacies, travel clinics, public health offices and some doctor's offices. For more information re HPV click here. If you have further questions, please consult with your immunization provider. To find a health unit near you click here.
